Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.76,0:32:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,self-style masters and there was some\Nthat wandered through town here not long
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.27,0:32:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,ago. All right. Okay. So,\Npractical spirituality amounts to study.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.64,0:32:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we look at all the list of qualified\Ncalibrated teachers and calibrated works
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.48,0:32:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we contemplate and meditate.\NSo, contemplation and meditation we have
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.88,0:32:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,talked about before.\NMeditation tends to take you out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.88,0:32:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,world and if you can find a time and\Nplace that is convenient. The difficulty
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.51,0:33:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,with meditation is life becomes\Nprogressively demanding and the amount
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.72,0:33:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of time that you all lot to it begins to\Ndiminish. I allotted an hour in the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.60,0:33:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,morning and an hour at night for some 20\Nor 25 years or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.36,0:33:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And I then gave it up to come out west\Nand meditate all day every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.72,0:33:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So went in the opposite direction. All\Nright.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.12,0:33:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation then is a very effective way.\NAnd of course there's many meditative
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.76,0:33:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,techniques. And uh the simpler the they\Nare the better. Contemplation is holding
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.08,0:33:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a thing in mind and and asking God uh to\Nreveal to the Holy Spirit to reveal to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.84,0:33:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you the the what is the meaning of that?\NWhat is the significance of that? uh
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.64,0:34:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to be as a basic rule if you only need\None thing contemplative and meditative
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.00,0:34:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,uh I would say to be compassionate\Ntowards all of life to be compassionate
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.96,0:34:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,uh towards all of life in all of its\Nexpressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.15,0:34:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You can love chocolate or vanilla. You\Ncan love strawberry or vanilla. You can
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.96,0:34:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,love liberals and conservatives.\NUh so to be compassionate, you begin to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.96,0:34:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,see that everything and everyone is just\Nbeing what they are. They're only being
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.24,0:34:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what they are. So what is there to\Nforgive?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.52,0:34:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You would say, well, the person has the\Noption to be all other than they are. If
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.80,0:34:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,they had a real option to be other than\Nthey are, they would be other than they
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.39,0:34:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,are.\NThey don't have an option to be other
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.59,0:34:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,than they are. That's a hypothetical\Nproposition you project onto people and
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.63,0:34:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Well, they could be this way or\Nthey could be that way." No, they can't
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.64,0:35:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,be.\NEverybody is innocent because everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.80,0:35:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is only being to the fullest that which\Nthey are capable of being. And if they
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.59,0:35:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,were capable of being other than that\Nwhich they are, they would be
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.52,0:35:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,right.\NIf everybody was capable of being a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.92,0:35:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,millionaire, everybody would be one.\NYeah. If everybody could run the nine
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.40,0:35:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what it whatch\Ntook me longer than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.72,0:35:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How about the 10-minute mile?\NWhen you get to be 80, you got to make
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.76,0:35:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the 10-minute mile,\N>> right? Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.44,0:35:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemplation then allows you to hold\Nthe thing in mind and just question it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.11,0:35:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's like you look it over. It's\Nlooking at a flower from different
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.40,0:36:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,levels. And different times you see\Ndifferent light shining forth and a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.52,0:36:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,greater understanding. Meditation is a\Nmore intense way of doing that. The
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.11,0:36:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,balance of faith and reason then you\Nknow the great spiritual teachers of all
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.72,0:36:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,time uh whose name I forget\Nbalance of faith and reason was the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.16,0:36:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,great Catholic theologian\NThomas Aquinus. Oh yes. And I went to a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.40,0:36:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the university I went to was by uh the\Nteachers there were all members of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.59,0:36:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Jesuits.\N>> Jesuits. Yeah. Right. And Thomas Aquinus
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.68,0:36:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,was a very big uh and Thomas Aquinus\Ncaliber is quite high in the 700s. All
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.92,0:36:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,right. So to become a a thing instead of\Njust knowing about it. So many people
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.40,0:37:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,can repeat back a dictim. they know\Nabout it, but that it's it's a further
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.72,0:37:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,step to become it.\NTherefore, it's best to is not only is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.16,0:37:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,necessary to avoid all hatred doctrines,\Nall things that teach hatred, teach
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.00,0:37:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred,\Nbe watchful of spiritual ego and and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.72,0:37:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the the downfall of a lot of\Npeople is uh the idea that I know. I
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.52,0:37:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,know. The minute your mind says I know\Nuh you're in trouble. It's best to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.96,0:37:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,merely merely claim that you've heard.\NYou've heard. I've heard. I have heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.04,0:37:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha said I have heard. And he\Ndidn't say I know anything. He said I
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.80,0:37:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,have heard. That means this is a aspect\Nof reality that you don't really
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.04,0:37:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehend until you've contemplated it.\NUh sometimes for 40 or 50 years, you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.92,0:37:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,know what I mean? By\Nage 80, a few of the things start to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.64,0:38:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,sink through.\NYou think, "Oh, I know what you mean."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.28,0:38:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes. Spiritual ego is the idea that\NI know. I know. So, the only problem
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.16,0:38:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,with advanced study is the presumption\Nthat one knows that you can safeguard it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.83,0:38:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,by saying, "I have heard. I have heard.\NI've even heard that you can calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.35,0:38:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of consciousness. I have heard.\NI've heard that. And of course, many
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.44,0:38:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,people disagree with it. God bless them.\NI don't want people who disagree with me
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.24,0:38:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,agreeing with me.\NIt's better to thyself be true. If you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.44,0:38:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,doubt it, then doubt it and have a good\Ntime doubting it. You have a perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.20,0:38:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,right to be wrong.\NThe spiritually aligned person is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.11,0:38:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,attracted to beauty in all of its forms.\Nthe beauty of nature, the beauty of all
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.16,0:39:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that exists.\NThere is a a time that when you go
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.00,0:39:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond the ordinary\Nand the beauty of everything that exists
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.11,0:39:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes overwhelming. The beauty of\Nevery animal, every bush, every tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.83,0:39:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All things are divinity. All things are\NGod. And all that happens is you begin
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.00,0:39:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize the essence that the essence\Nof all things are God.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.24,0:39:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence of all that exists is God is\Ndivinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.88,0:39:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nwhen you walk through the woods,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.68,0:39:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the tree is aware of your walking by.\NThe tree is aware of your existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.00,0:39:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NThe tree is aware of your existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.80,0:39:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is alive is aware of your\Nexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.28,0:40:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Aha.\NYou see how important your existence is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.04,0:40:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what you have become radiates out\Ninto the world and by a field effect
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.20,0:40:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,influences everything around you.\NIf the percentage of people in the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.64,0:40:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,population who are meditating are over\N1% the crime rate drops down 90%. If
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.52,0:40:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,only 1% of the population is meditating\Nthe crime rate drops profoundly. Isn't
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.07,0:40:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that interesting?\NThat was done a study by the followers
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.44,0:40:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of Maharishi yogi.\NYeah. That of over 1%. So when I came to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.52,0:40:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sedona, this was this place attracted\Nonly spiritually uh motivated people for
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.68,0:40:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,decades. There was the local business\Npeople and then there were all the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.44,0:40:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual people.\NSo the percentage of people who were
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.68,0:40:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,meditating here was probably 50% or\Nsomething.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.92,0:41:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And crime never happened in Sedona. None\Nof us ever took our I never took the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.52,0:41:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,ignition switch out of the car and you\Nparked it in front of the store and you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.92,0:41:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,just left the keys in it. Nobody ever\Nbothered. Never locked the door at
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.96,0:41:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,night. Never took the key out of the\Ncar. Nothing ever disappeared and the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.88,0:41:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,crime rate was zero.\NDidn't need any cops because nobody ever
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.28,0:41:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,got arrested for anything because nobody\Never did anything illegal.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.40,0:41:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The wildest thing you could do would be\Nto go over the speed limit a couple
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.92,0:41:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,miles an hour.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.04,0:41:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty then attracts people and uh\Nyou influence everything around you by
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.76,0:41:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you have become.\NSo you don't have to feel like you have
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.16,0:41:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to be out there doing good deeds. Good\Ndeedism
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.28,0:41:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the dogooders.\NThere's a book. It's really a knockout
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.44,0:41:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,called the dogooders.\NI forget who wrote it. Some lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.83,0:42:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, she tracks all these do goodter\Nideas down through the decades to see
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.11,0:42:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what actually happens. I don't know. And\Nactually what happens is usually the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.59,0:42:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,opposite. You know what I'm saying?\NAnyway, uh so you don't have to be uh do
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.59,0:42:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,good. Uh in fact, it's best not to do\Nany good. I I advise people
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.31,0:42:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,please do not do any good. Okay? Give me\Na promise. you will not stop doing good
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.04,0:42:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in this world. Okay? Just be what you\Nare to the fullest extent that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.24,0:42:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,be that. Why? Because by doing that, you\Nautomatically automatically raise the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.35,0:42:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness of all of\Nmankind. And mankind has no defense
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.44,0:42:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,against that. If I say you all have to\Ndonate to charity, you got everybody's
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.64,0:42:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,going to have their resentment right\Naway. You say, "Oh, I want to donate to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.56,0:42:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,charity." You don't really want to\Ndonate to charity.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.96,0:43:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you got a guilt complex, you're\Nkind of some kind of a nut job.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.96,0:43:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The bigger the check, the bigger the\Nguilt complex. Buy your way into heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.64,0:43:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, that's why churches are\Nwellendowed. There's enough people with
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.76,0:43:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,enough guilt to write big checks before\Nthey go.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.92,0:43:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked my local church, "How are you\Nfixed financially?" He says, "No
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.44,0:43:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,problem. No problem.\Nfind your way into heaven, right? I
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.20,0:43:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,think it does count when you get to\Nheaven. I think it does. You know that
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.83,0:43:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you you you did feel sorry that you were\Nsuch an sob. You know that check for
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.44,0:43:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,20,000 did help the church. You know,\Nall right. So music cathedrals, people
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.20,0:43:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,who are spiritually oriented become\Nattracted to music and we pointed out
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.92,0:43:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,before that tends to shift the brain\Nfunction. The the spiritual energy to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.28,0:44:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,right brain and the dendrites the\Ndendrites in the brain are constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.83,0:44:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,forming and and then dying. The brain\Neven in old age is constantly producing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.16,0:44:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,new neurons all the time. And if they're\Nnot used, disuse, they they cretinize.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.07,0:44:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They they show up and go away. If\Nthey're used, then they they these these
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.52,0:44:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,neurons which are going around will\Nconnect with each other because now they
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.40,0:44:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,form a track and and it's a working\Ntract. So the way to take advantage of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.00,0:44:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that, no matter how old you are, your\Nbrain is still producing new neurons all
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.92,0:44:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the time.\NYou can't use old age as an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.20,0:44:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The the brain is producing neurons\Neven into advanced age. Even this this
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.20,0:44:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,creature here\NBammo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.31,0:44:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the world better look out now.\NBoy,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.16,0:45:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I can feel those neurons twisting and\Nwrithing and doing a dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.40,0:45:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the dance of the neurons.\NThe dance of the neurons. Your neurons
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.28,0:45:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,are saying, "Please feed me more beauty.\NPlease feed me more beautiful movies and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.16,0:45:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,gorgeous things in this world to\Nappreciate. And priests help me to see
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.59,0:45:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the essence of things rather than the\Nperception.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.20,0:45:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you constantly ask to see it,\Neventually what is revealed to you if
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.80,0:45:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you live through the experience is\Nwhat's eventually revealed
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.68,0:46:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is that all things are God.\NEverything is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.48,0:46:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All is God. There is nothing but God.\NPeriod. And see that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.24,0:46:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing but God. Resist.\NWell, look for God when that's all there
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.24,0:46:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is.\NSo then it dawns on you one day when
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.52,0:46:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you're looking at things, the essence of\Ndivinity shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.31,0:46:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've discussed that moment when it\Nhappened in my life. And suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.20,0:46:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the divinity of all things shown forth\Nwith such a brilliance that it was
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.28,0:46:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it it laid me out for some years. I\Ndon't think I could do anything for a
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.56,0:46:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,few years. Anyway,\Nthat spiritual intention then will bring
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.28,0:46:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,forth that awareness that all things are\NGod. All things are God.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.35,0:47:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All things. Because the essence of all\Nthat exists is nonlinear. What you're
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.48,0:47:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at is the linear which defines\Ndifference. What you're not seeing is
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.96,0:47:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that to exist the first requirement is\Nto exist. And to exist is nonlinear. It
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.76,0:47:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,has no form. The essence of existence is\Nformless and is actually divinity. The
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.56,0:47:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,essence of God is equally this arm,\Nequally this foot, equally this stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.40,0:47:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,equally everyone present here.\NNext chart will be done soon. Uh study,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.56,0:47:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,contemplation and meditation, faith and\Nreason. We did that one. We were talking
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.96,0:47:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,about a beauty. Be watchful of\Nreligionism
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.00,0:47:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and practice the virtues, the great\Ncommandments. avoid the seven deadly
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.24,0:47:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sins. All right. Practice of the virtues\Nthen becomes sort of automatic. You
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.24,0:48:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,know, if you're angry at something, you\Nforgive yourself for being angry. You
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.00,0:48:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to ask God to see it differently.\NThen you see its innocence and you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.96,0:48:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,forgive it. So therefore, it's the to\Npractice the great commandments. We say,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.20,0:48:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, everybody knows that\Nto bear false witness against your
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.20,0:48:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,neighbor. Isn't that one of the ten\Ncommandments?" Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.20,0:48:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That's violated every day on television.\NEvery day on television,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.07,0:48:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you can hear false\Ndistortion of what the other person said
