Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.72,0:50:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,only see how it appears to you. So there\Nwould be no point to try to change it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.28,0:50:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're not changing something\Nthat is. You're only changing something
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.11,0:50:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that you see.\NThat's why the famous saying of there's
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.07,0:50:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,no point of trying to change the world\Nyou see because the world you see
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.83,0:50:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't even exist.\NTrying to save the world from what? From
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.92,0:50:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,what you have projected uh onto the\Nworld and what you think you are seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.04,0:50:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, many people have earned the\Nright to undo negative karma
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.16,0:50:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh to gain positive karma. So if the\Npurpose of this world is
