Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.20,0:51:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, avoidance of the deadly\Nsins deglamorize
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.40,0:51:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,attractions. Uh, today's world\Ncapitalizes on the glamorization of
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.52,0:51:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,attractions. And what's the last one?\NBecause we'll come back to that later.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.28,0:51:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\Nall right. We'll come back to that
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.55,0:51:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,later.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.52,0:51:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so what we're saying today is very\Nsimple.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.24,0:51:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is God.\NGod is the power to become and manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.16,0:51:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as anything and everything\Nto see the divinity of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.24,0:52:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So you say, "Dear God, I ask to see the\Ntruth of everything as it is in truth. I
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.76,0:52:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,asked to see the essence of everything\Nrather than a projected perception or
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.44,0:52:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,some programmed\Nglamorized version. So out of that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.24,0:52:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,simplicity and that humility, you say,\N"I don't know anything."
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.92,0:52:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The dumber you are, the better.\NWhen you're convinced that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.72,0:52:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,hopelessly endlessly stupid, you're\Nmaking good progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.00,0:52:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The dumber we are, the better we are.\NAll right, so we'll take a break and
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.11,0:52:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll meet you again after lunch.\NWhere are we? We're right here.
