Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.04,1:21:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,bathrooms in your house doesn't help you\Nwhen you got to go wow wow. You got to
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.88,1:21:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,go wow wow.\NI've lived uh in in all those different
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.76,1:21:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,varieties\Nand I also knew people who lived in the
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.23,1:21:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,extreme of them multi-billionaires\Nand frankly they were no happier.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.08,1:21:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Their living room was no more\Ncomfortable. I sat in the chairs of some
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.08,1:21:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of the most wealthy people in the world\Nand frankly
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.71,1:21:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,felt the same.\NYou go to the bathroom, it flushes the
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.64,1:21:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,sink.\NSo, what you're talking about is the
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.48,1:21:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,superficial trappings of it all. So,\Nlet's say we have the emotional security
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.44,1:21:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that the stock market is not going is\Nnot going to drop.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.84,1:21:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh boy, now I'm happier. It's not going\Nto drop.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.04,1:21:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh boy, I was worried the stock market\Nis going to drop. I say, "No, it's not
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.88,1:22:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,going to drop." Say, "Oh boy. Oh boy, my\Nlife is saved. The stock market is not
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.15,1:22:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,going to drop." Oh, now we turn around.\NWe say, "Oh, that was wrong. The subm
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.04,1:22:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,market is going to drop." Oh, God. Was\Nmy retirement account. Uh, so you can't
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.04,1:22:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,let yourself, you know, I lived through\None depression, so I've seen it go up
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.23,1:22:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and see it go down. And frankly, you ate\Nmore peanut butter than steak during the
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.36,1:22:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,depression, but that was really the main\Ndifference. And uh we drove an older
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.00,1:22:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,car, you know, it was a 1927 Model A\NFord,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.08,1:22:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which now is a collector's item. I wish\NI had it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.76,1:22:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,$35,000 for it.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.44,1:22:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's considerably what you\Ncompare yourself with in fantasy with
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.32,1:22:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,others.\NIf you say with your own people that are
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.40,1:22:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,just like you, everybody is having\Npeanut butter sandwiches because they
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.71,1:23:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,can't afford sig. And it's not a\Nproblem. You know, we never bought a uh
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.08,1:23:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,something to put your sandwich in. You\Nsaved the wax paper that the bread came
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.60,1:23:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in and you wrapped your sandwiches to go\Nto school in them and you use the same
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.76,1:23:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,bread wrapper for about two, three\Nmonths before it all wore out.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.63,1:23:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So the pleasure of life then the\Npleasure of life is not dependent on the
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.88,1:23:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,externals. The externals are nice. It's\Nnice to think you got all that money.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.60,1:23:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course I always remember mama's\Nsavings account. Everybody knows that
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.44,1:23:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,story\Nuh through depression. You know the
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.56,1:23:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,family would worry about uh it was a\Nfamous story. I think it was published
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.88,1:23:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Reader's Digest.\Nand they they would all worry about
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.96,1:23:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,money and the the woman would say, "I've\Ngot plenty of money in my bank account.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.28,1:23:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it." Oh, the kids\Nwould feel okay again. And then after
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.96,1:23:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the the lady died many years later, they\Nfound she never had a bank account. All
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.67,1:23:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,those years, it doesn't even exist. But\Nshe would tell them that the money was
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.88,1:23:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the bank account. Don't worry, if we\Nrun out of money, we'll take it out
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.00,1:24:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,mother's bank account. So that to me,\Nmother's bank account is probably the
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.32,1:24:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,best explanation of wealth and money and\Nprestige and all those things that they
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.67,1:24:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,have that magical sense of reassurance\Nthat you're not really in danger, that
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.88,1:24:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you're really in a in safety. So I think\Nwhat people are really worried about in
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.76,1:24:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the current economic situation is\Nsafety. Really safety, not so much
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.00,1:24:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,luxury. You're not worrying about\Nwhether you can get a new cat Cadillac
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.28,1:24:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,next year or not. Yeah. you're really\Nworrying about survival and security. So
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.80,1:24:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,once you reassure yourself about\Nsurvival and security uh then the rest
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.44,1:24:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of it is just the excitement and drama\Nof life. One of the reasons you decided
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.04,1:24:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to be reborn is you want the excitement\Nand the drama drama of life. I mean this
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.67,1:24:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is the best TV program around you.\NHe turned on the news in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.40,1:25:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Bloomberg says, "The Dow dropped 300\Npoints yesterday." Oh, I said, "Susan,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.15,1:25:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,guess what, honey? The Dow dropped 300\Npoints." She says, "Where where did they
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.71,1:25:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,drop it?\NThe NASDAQ is up 122 points." Wow. Isn't
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.71,1:25:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that exciting, huh? Yeah, that's\Nexciting. No, it makes life fun. The
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.92,1:25:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,drama of life makes it fun and exciting.\NThat's why we're all riveted to the
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.04,1:25:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,screen of our own life, watching it\Nunroll before us. We're just excited by
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.44,1:25:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the drama of it all.\N>> Will old Doc and Susan make it around
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.52,1:25:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the corner there or not? Oh, they made\Nit. Oh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.00,1:25:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He actually is there. Yeah.\N>> The drama of life. Yeah. So, life is one
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.32,1:25:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,endless drama. You know, we we gave in\Nsome book someplace about 42 different
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.76,1:26:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,interpretations of the meaning and\Nsignificance of life and and one of them
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.40,1:26:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of course is drama. The the drama of\Nlife, the excitement of it, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.15,1:26:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the vital energy of it, you know. Yeah.\NSo because all of us have this emotional
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.96,1:26:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,level in us, then you're saying that\Nactually that plays out as part of the
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.12,1:26:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,drama\N>> in different situations.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.88,1:26:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, it's it can also be trained out of\Nyou. It depends on whether you value it
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.19,1:26:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or not.\N>> And uh traditionally women have been
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.12,1:26:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,more accepting of the emotional side of\Nthe life and men tend to be more the
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.44,1:26:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,logical.\NIf you're at a business company and a
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.60,1:26:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,certain bill want gets to has to be paid\Nand the means of paying it has to be
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.04,1:26:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,derived, nobody cares how you feel about\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.60,1:26:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody cares how you feel about it.\N>> Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.60,1:26:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> How you feel about is your problem. The\Ncompany doesn't want to care doesn't
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.36,1:26:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,want to know how you feel about it. They\Njust say, you know, we got to have
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.71,1:27:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody go to Baltimore and and meet\Nwith this company and settle this issue.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.04,1:27:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh they have no care. So men learn to\Ntrain out the emotions, pay less
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.71,1:27:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,attention to them. They may still have\Nthem, but they're minimal and you can't
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.28,1:27:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,base a decision on how you feel about\Nit. Now on on the other hand, there are
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.80,1:27:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,business executives who are also quite\Nintuitive. They can they'll intuit it
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.63,1:27:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,how the market's going to work in this\Nparticular area. But that's not emotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.19,1:27:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's intuition. intuition is putting\Ntogether the non-verbal and non
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.32,1:27:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,uh describable\Nhow the energy fields are moving. So,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.96,1:27:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,uh you you can be quite intuitive\Nwithout necessarily being emotional
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.80,1:27:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,about it. You know, it looks it looks\Nlike the world may get worse before it
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.12,1:27:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,gets better. Well, there's no point of\Nbeing upset by it. Just say, "Well,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.36,1:27:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,probably the world's going to get a\Nlittle worse before it gets better." So
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.60,1:28:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is that okay with everybody? Could be\Nworse before it gets better.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.52,1:28:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Just think when it does get better, how\Nrelieved we'll be.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.60,1:28:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um I was going to talk to you about, you\Nknow, that high experience that I had.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.84,1:28:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Um a lot of times we get emails from\Npeople that say, you know, I want you to
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.67,1:28:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I have this high experience and I want\Nyou to calibrate it. Well, in my
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.08,1:28:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,experience, that's the last thing I\Nwanted to do is calibrate it because I
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.67,1:28:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,knew it was a high experience. So, how\Ndo you how do you tell these people that
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.44,1:28:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,email us and say, "I've had this very\Nhigh experience."
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.12,1:28:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, they're all unique. Each one is a\Nspecific.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.23,1:28:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, they want to be unique, though.\NSome of them want to be unique.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.67,1:28:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. They're looking for specialness.\NAnd a lot of times that they're
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.96,1:28:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,legitimate, too. They're legitimate\Nquestions. And then there's questions
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.44,1:28:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of confusion\N>> right
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.00,1:28:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and don't forget the\N>> but those I can understand but
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.96,1:29:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,>> the human psyche is quite comp you know\Ncomplicated. So is a feeling of elation
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.15,1:29:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,due to hyper because you're manic or is\Nit because you're you know advanced
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.04,1:29:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,conscious consciousness. So some of them\NI I look them over and I always ask
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.08,1:29:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,using whatever means I have\Nwhat is that level of this experience
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.67,1:29:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and how best to to give an answer back\Nto the person so that it's helpful. I
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.52,1:29:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want to discourage somebody and\Ntell them you know that was a delusion
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.48,1:29:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you just had\Nsmoking that magic weed and sticks of
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.36,1:29:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,coffee. you know,\N>> um, a lot of people though, um, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.44,1:29:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it's real to them.\N>> Yes, they're that experiential.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.52,1:29:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Very real to them whether it's\Ndelusional or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.15,1:29:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I never discount, uh, the reality of the\Nexperiential to anybody,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.12,1:29:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,>> but what they're asking for is to\Ncontextualize it. What does it mean? And
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.15,1:30:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I uh I if it's something that's not\Nuh when I tell them it's evolutionary
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.19,1:30:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that these are these are uh energies and\Nexperiences that arise through spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.28,1:30:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution and maybe and often this is\Ntrue when you start looking within you
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.08,1:30:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,start activating energy fields that are\Nnot ordinarily activated
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.48,1:30:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and you can bring up an awful lot of\Nstuff when you start searching within
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.44,1:30:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore\NI think what they need is reassurance.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.12,1:30:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So I usually will I'll check the reality\Nof it and I'll say well once you look
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.60,1:30:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,within you can bring up stacks you know\Nin an S they call it stacks you know if
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.88,1:30:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you start looking at guilt you've got\Nstacks of guilt not just the guilt about
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.60,1:30:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,this but you got you got guilt upon\Nguilt upon guilt. So if you start
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.08,1:30:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,pulling up guilt you can get overwhelmed\Nwith guilt. If you pull up anger, if you
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.71,1:30:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,pull up any of the so-called negative\Nfeelings, you find that you've got
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.12,1:30:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,stacks of them. And then of course later\Non you discover that you also have
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.67,1:31:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,stacks about good feelings.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.80,1:31:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I think about my doggy right now\Nand I feel warm rush of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.19,1:31:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> See?\NUh and then you think of animals that
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.19,1:31:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,have attacked you in the past and you\Ncan think about them and suddenly you're
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.04,1:31:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,scared.\NSo there's stacks. When I was a paper
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.19,1:31:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,boy, you know, I had a long route in\NWisconsin and there was a couple of
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.12,1:31:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,customers that had mad dogs and guard\Ndogs. And as you got near these people's
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.60,1:31:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,property, I get my paper all ready to\Nthrow. And I'd take my feet and hold it
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.12,1:31:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,up off the paddles, put them up on the\Nhandlebars, and I get going real fast,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.32,1:31:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,put my feet up on the handlebars, and\NI'd throw the paper like this and keep
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.28,1:31:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,going because I\Nwould tear your leg off if you got a
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.12,1:31:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,chance.\NAnd I thought these idiot people that
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.88,1:31:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,keep dogs like that on their premises. I\Nmean, what kind of people are these, you
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.48,1:31:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,know, that that harbor these vicious\Ndogs? I mean, it says a lot for the
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.80,1:32:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,owner. The dog can't help being what it\Nis. But many many a night I kept my feet
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.32,1:32:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,on the handlebars and went like hell to\Nthrow that paper.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.56,1:32:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\N>> so how do you so compassion, how can you
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.12,1:32:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,show compassion without looking weak?\N>> Uh, it's not a matter of showing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.48,1:32:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a matter of feeling it from within.\N>> Well, how do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.60,1:32:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I mean, for instance, the dog that comes\Nat me to tear my ankle off. I know he
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.76,1:32:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,can't help it. You know, he's trained to\Nbe that way. He's trained to be a
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.71,1:32:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,watchdog.\NUh, so I don't hate the dog. On the
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.32,1:32:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,other hand, I'm not an idiot. I'm not\Ngoing to put my foot there for him to
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.12,1:32:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,chew on.\NSo, how you how you see it and how you
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.04,1:32:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,react to it are two different things.\NI usually see most things being what
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.08,1:33:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they are and that they can't really be\Nany different than they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.56,1:33:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, like for instance, I I know that\Num prayer is is always um good to use in
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.08,1:33:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,those situations because\N>> um I've seen it too many times in our
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.40,1:33:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,life where we can't find something and\Nso Dave will pray for a miracle and all
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.67,1:33:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of a sudden there it is.\N>> It comes out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.71,1:33:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It wasn't for the Holy Spirit. I\Nwouldn't be able to get dressed in the
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.84,1:33:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,morning.\NI lose everything. I can't find it. I
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.92,1:33:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,can't see anymore. So, I can't see it.\NSo, I say I ask God, "God, where is it?"
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.23,1:33:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And all a sudden, I like know where it\Nis. And I reach out. There it is. My
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.60,1:33:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,golly.\N>> But it happens over and over in our
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.28,1:33:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,lives.\N>> It drives you crazy. I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.44,1:33:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And tough to live with. Living with an\Nidiot is
